Some tips on how to stay cool and what to do during a heatwave. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - South Africans can look forward to cooler temperatures next week. A blistering heatwave gripped parts of the country from Friday but temperatures are expected to drop on Monday. READ: Tshwane residents urged to save water According to the weather service, the heatwave should break by Sunday night. Watch the video above for some tips on how to stay cool and what to do during a heatwave.